<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="d7ea09db-8151-44d6-b691-f1d4a30092da" >

    <ul> 
 <li><strong><a href="http://oin.ouinternational.ca/programs" target="_blank">OIN Study India Program<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link, opens in new window</span></a>&nbsp;</strong>-&nbsp;A month-long immersion program held in August at Shiv Nadar University, Noida (National Capital Region). Offers students the opportunity to learn about India’s history, culture, politics, social structure, architecture, fine arts, religions, and more.</li> 
 <li><strong><a href="http://oin.ouinternational.ca/programs" target="_blank">OIN Short-term Study Program<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link, opens in new window</span></a>&nbsp;</strong>-&nbsp;A two to three month research program that can be undertaken at any time in the calendar year. It is intended for students with defined projects in the arts, humanities, social sciences, sciences, engineering, management and technology. The on-campus project is conducted under the supervision of a professor at an OIN partner college or university in India.</li> 
</ul>
    





