    <ul> 
 <li><a href="http://ojs.ouinternational.ca/apply" target="_blank"><strong>OJS Summer Research Program</strong><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link, opens in new window</span></a> - Opportunity for undergraduate and graduate students to carry out a four-month research project at one of the ten participating universities in Jiangsu Province.</li> 
 <li><strong><a href="http://ojs.ouinternational.ca/sites/default/files/OJS%20Summer%20Programs%20pamphlet%202019.pdf" target="_blank"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span>OJS Summer Food Culture Program<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, opens in new window</span></a></strong>- Four weeks (mid May - mid June) held at Jiangnan University that aims to deepen students’ understanding of food culture in China, including lectures, tours and visits, and activities with local students.</li> 
 <li><strong><a href="http://ojs.ouinternational.ca/sites/default/files/OJS%20Summer%20Programs%20pamphlet%202019.pdf" target="_blank"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span>OJS Social Change in China Course<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, opens in new window</span></a></strong>&nbsp;- Four weeks in July held at Xi’an Jiaotong-Liverpool University. Lectures, Seminar discussions, presentations, and group projects on social change in China, including Chinese language classes provided on most days.</li> 
 <li><strong><a href="http://ojs.ouinternational.ca/sites/default/files/OJS%20Summer%20Programs%20pamphlet%202019.pdf" target="_blank"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span>OJS Intensive Mandarin Course&nbsp;<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, opens in new window</span></a>&nbsp;</strong>- Four weeks (mid May - mid June) held at Nanjing University of the Arts and available to students from basic to mid-level Mandarin competence. Includes weekly cultural activities and visits as well as a one-to-one language partner.</li> 
 <li><a href="http://ojs.ouinternational.ca/sites/default/files/OJS%20Summer%20Programs%20pamphlet%202019.pdf" target="_blank"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span><strong>OJS Chinese Language &amp; Culture Program</strong><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, opens in new window</span></a>&nbsp;- Four weeks in July held at Yangzhou University. No knowledge of Mandarin required. Survival Chinese based on students’ language proficiency, including cultural activities and visits.</li> 
 <li><strong><a href="http://ojs.ouinternational.ca/sites/default/files/OJS%20Summer%20Programs%20pamphlet%202019.pdf" target="_blank"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span>OJS Summer Design School<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, opens in new window</span></a>&nbsp;</strong>- Four weeks from June 17 to July 14 held at Jiangnan University. Designed to create an interdisciplinary practice for design students from various backgrounds to explore the different emerging issues along with new technologies and services to create a unique cultural experience of the traditional and the new cultures in China.</li> 
</ul>
    





