<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="d5616ceb-ffc6-432d-baac-485708c2e6d5" >

    <h3>Applying to a OUI Summer Program</h3> 
<p><strong>Step 1 - Choose your program:</strong> It is your responsibility to research which program and destination would best fit your needs. Remember to pay close attention to what is included in program fees (housing, meals, tuition?), and to take into account the cost of flights and additional entertainment.</p> 
<p>Students have in the past been able to receive credit for <strong>some programs</strong> through the <a href="/content/ryerson/curriculum-advising/curriculum-exceptions/letter-permission.html">Letter of Permission process.</a> If you are interested in potentially receiving credit for a OUI summer program, you will need to complete an <a href="/content/ryerson/curriculum-advising/curriculum-exceptions/letter-permission.html">LOP application</a> before you leave.</p> 
<p><strong>Step 2 - Prepare Your Application:</strong> Each program has its own application form and requirements, that you can find on the relevant program website (sometimes located under the Apply tab at the top of the program page). Make sure to carefully review the instruction found on each program website, complete the necessary forms and gather any additional supporting documents well before the application deadline.</p> 
<p><strong>If your application requires a transcript:</strong></p> 
<p><strong>Step 3 - Submit You Application:</strong> Submit a <strong>hard copy</strong> of your completed OUI application package to the <a href="/content/ryerson/ri/contact-us.html">Ryerson International Office</a> before the application deadline.</p> 
<p>If you have any questions about the OUI summer Programs, please contact Ryerson International at <a href="mailto:rihelp@ryerson.ca">rihelp@ryerson.ca</a>.<br> </p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#d5616ceb-ffc6-432d-baac-485708c2e6d5");});</script></div>

				</div>

